Milk Texturing v2 + NEW BLOG POST OUT !! 

In 2023, I had the opportunity to travel with @milklabco , sharing my tips and tricks for texturing and pouring plant-based milks. I ran workshops at various trade shows such as MICE 2022, @foodserviceaustralia (Food Service Australia), and @finefoodexpo (Fine Foods). This is what we discussed.

Are you familiar with all the variables that you don't have control over in the environment when it comes to texturing milk? 

The goal is to give people control over the amount of milk they pour and the amount of froth they can get, as well as how to control the jug. One of the biggest issues is that people are trained to make milk differently. This is what gave me the idea for this graph. With this graph, you can apply the theory of how milk is textured, no matter how strong your steam wand is ‚Ä¶..

A, B, and C represent where you place the tip in relation to the jug from a bird's eye view

The difference between left and right is only really going to make a difference in which direction the milk spins. If you put the tip on the left side, it will spin counterclockwise. If you put it on the right side, it will spin clockwise. Positions A, B, and C = slow, medium, and fast. Based on the power of the steam, you decide where to place it. But for most commercial machines, you'll be safe starting at B (pictured).

Sharing this around would be greatly appreciated

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
-Summertime Orange & Cherry Blossom Dessert-

Peach and apricot compote, paired with orange blossom honey with airy puff pastries and custard. A multitude of flavours and textures in a dessert form. Honestly l, I‚Äôve not had such a great dessert in a while (pats back). üòù guys, save this recipe if you have ran out of ideas on what to bring/cook for your next gathering. 

Recipe:
Ingredients:‚Ä®1 pckt frozen puff pastry
70g custard powder
400ml water
3 tbsp sugar 

Berries compote:
2 peaches (diced)
3 apricots (diced)
2 tbsp Orange Blossom Honey( or regular honey)
2 tbsp brown sugar 
20ml water

Garnish:
Cherries
Thyme

Instruction:‚Ä®1. Cut puff pastries into 4cm x 8cm size.
2. Arrange on baking tray and use another baking tray to sit on top so pastries doesn‚Äôt fluff too much. 
3. Bake in oven at 220 degree for 20mins. Set a side.
4. To prepare fruit compote:‚Ä®Add in peaches, apricot, sugar and water  and cook for 15minutes, add in honey and continue stirring for 3 minutes until sauce is thickened. 
5. To prepare custard filling:‚Ä®Mix custard powder and water together and stir under medium heat for 5minutes. Continue stirring vigourously until thickened. Put in piping bag and set aside.
6. Assemble by piping custard on pastry puff, followed by a generous amount of fruit compote, repeat the steps for another layer and garnish with fresh cut cherries and thyme.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Breakfast Wrap
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Inspired by the classic Grilled Chicken and Eggs sandwich, here‚Äôs my twist on this recipe using Mission Wraps! Don‚Äôt remember the last time I made such an amazing sandwich. This recipe is so easy to make and fuss-free to eat, great for breakfast or even as a snack.
 
I'm using Mission Onion and Chive Wraps and it definitely adds a better bite and flavour compared to bread.

Grilled Black Pepper Chicken & Scrambled Eggs Wrap

Ingredients:
2 Mission Supersoft Onion & Chive Wraps
100 gm Cherry Tomatoes, halved
2 Eggs
1 tsp Butter
50 gm Spinach
2 tbsp Molasses
1 tbsp Chilli Sauce
Mayonnaise, for drizzling
Salt and Pepper, to taste

For Grilled Chicken:
400 gm Chicken Breast
2 tsp Oregano
1 tsp Paprika
1 tsp Garlic Powder
1 tsp Pepper
1 tsp Salt

Instructions:
1. In a bowl, mix oregano, paprika, garlic powder, pepper and salt. Fully coat the chicken and marinate for 2 hours in the fridge.
2. Remove the marinated chicken from the fridge and place it on a heat proof pan and roast in the oven at 180ÔÇ∞C for 15 minutes.
3. Once done, remove the chicken from the pan and slice it. Set aside.
4. In a bowl, mix the molasses and spinach together and set aside.
5. In a pan over low heat, add cherry tomatoes and lightly stir fry for 1-2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Once done, remove from pan and set aside.
6. In a small bowl, crack the eggs and add salt and pepper and whisk the egg mixture with a fork.
7. In a pan over medium heat, melt butter and add the egg mixture. Once the egg becomes fluffy, remove from pan and set aside.

To assemble:
1. Warm Mission Onion & Chive Wraps in a pan for 10-15 seconds each side.
2. Spread the chilli sauce evenly on the wraps then top with spinach, cherry tomatoes, scrambled eggs & sliced chicken breast.
3. Drizzle some mayo and fold the wraps using baking paper and tie each ends with a string.
4. Cut the folded wraps into halves and serve.
